name: I was deep in a dream

metadata.name: 12:38 a.m.
metadata.description:
“Source of our feelings is images, while in dreams the source of the images is feelings”.
These are self-portraits that I let become dreams.
Camera, tripod and I. Nobody else.

The photographs are using the matrix to create beautiful jumping moments. Before each jump, I closed my eyes. Background behind the figure, blurred spots, tree branches – that’s what I saw. I strive for understanding: is our world a dream or real?
Three photographs and performance acts remind us about real and temporary, dreams and reveries.
Jumping moments have titles provided  next to each artwork.

Artwork by Daria Chemakina
